
<div class="pricing-header">
  <div class="pricing-header-container">
    <h1>
      Affordable plans for everyone
    </h1>
    <h2>
      We provide you and your school with the full set of technology,
  support and learning resources needed to support the computing curriculum.
    </h2>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="pricing-slider">
  <%= partial 'slider' %>
  <div class="action-buttons">
    <%= link_to 'Start trial', '/p/signup', class: 'button button-large button-action' %>
    <%= link_to 'Contact us', '/', class: 'button button-large button-dark' %>
  </div>
</div>

<hr/>

<div class="pricing-faq">
  <div class="pricing-faq-header">
    <%= image_tag 'assets/pricing/faq.svg' %>
    <h2>Still some questions left?</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="pricing-faq-col pricing-faq-col-left">
    <div class="pricing-faq-entry">
      <h2>School licenses</h2>
      <p>
        School licences provide your school or education institution with
        a comprehensive, fully supported solution for your computing curriculum.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your school gets full access to the Codio platform for a defined number
        of users (teachers, administrators, students), including the IDE & coding
        platform, the curriculum aligned learning resources and support for organizations.
      </p>
      <p>
        Licences run for a full school academic year.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="pricing-faq-entry">
      <h2>Curriuclum course content</h2>
      <p>
        Codio's whole school licence is inclusive of access to the teaching
        resources for schools. Currently released courses have been designed
        for KS3 and GCSE Computing students (US grades 4-10) with KS2 content
        to follow shortly.
      </p>
      <p>
        In addition to the curriculum teaching resources for Python, An
        Introduction to Coding and An Introduction to Web Development, Codio
        and OCR will continue to release course content covering the full
        non-programming and programming elements of the UK curriculum.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="pricing-faq-col pricing-faq-col-right">
    <div class="pricing-faq-entry">
      <h2>Account owner</h2>
      <p>
        On sign up, you can create your school organisation account to which
        can be added accounts for your teaching colleagues, technicians and students.
      </p>
      <p>
        Account owners have administrative rights to manage the whole school
        licence including adding and removing teachers and students.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="pricing-faq-entry">
      <h2>Accounts</h2>
      <p>
        Each user account gets access to
        <ul>
          <li>
            the full IDE & coding platform with unlimited private project workspace
            and dedicated virtual servers
          </li>
          <li>
            access to our portfolio of learning resources
          </li>
          <li>
            organization support features (account owners only).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="pricing-faq-entry">
      <h2>Projects</h2>
      <p>
        Every user enjoys unlimited private projects e.g. programming
        projects or coursework. You can also create projects using Codio
        stacks or starter packs.
      </p>
      <p>
        We offer a comprehensive portfolio of pre configured stacks for a wide
        range of programming languages, frameworks, databases and other
        components (including Python, JavaScript & php)
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
